939
01:25:02,835 --> 01:25:04,378
I had no idea, Frank.

940
01:25:04,503 --> 01:25:07,047
Well, Captain,
I think it's only fair to tell you

941
01:25:07,172 --> 01:25:08,632
I've been to outside agencies.

942
01:25:08,757 --> 01:25:11,468
- I'll go to more if I have to.
- What outside agencies?

943
01:25:12,428 --> 01:25:15,764
Holy mother of God. Frank,
we wash our own laundry around here.

944
01:25:15,889 --> 01:25:18,058
You could be brought up on charges.

945
01:25:18,183 --> 01:25:21,979
The reality is we do not wash
our own laundry. It just gets dirtier.

946
01:25:22,104 --> 01:25:25,899
- You are in trouble.
- I don't care who gets it, including myself.

947
01:25:26,024 --> 01:25:29,278
- If I have to go to outside agencies...
- Stay away from outside agencies!

948
01:25:29,403 --> 01:25:31,280
Where am I gonna go?

949
01:25:31,405 --> 01:25:33,991
- Where am I gonna go?
- Wait till you hear from me!

950
01:25:34,116 --> 01:25:36,160
- I've been waiting for a year and a half.
- I'll get back to you.

951
01:25:36,285 --> 01:25:39,121
That's not enough. Where am I gonna go?

952
01:25:41,915 --> 01:25:44,084
It's my life, you fuck!

953
01:25:46,003 --> 01:25:49,423
Serpico, see Inspector Palmer.

954
01:25:57,723 --> 01:26:02,186
For this precinct, cases reported -
murder, 14 for August,

955
01:26:02,311 --> 01:26:06,023
20 for September... Serpico!

956
01:26:07,774 --> 01:26:09,651
Inspector Palmer?

957
01:26:12,029 --> 01:26:16,450
Deputy Chief Inspector Daley and
Inspector Gilbert are waiting to see you.

958
01:26:20,412 --> 01:26:22,414
Want to come to my office?

959
01:26:28,378 --> 01:26:30,088
Captain McClain called me.

960
01:26:31,298 --> 01:26:35,302
I've briefed Inspector Daley
and Inspector Gilbert on your allegations.

961
01:26:36,011 --> 01:26:38,972
The obvious question is this -
in all these months,

962
01:26:39,097 --> 01:26:40,766
why didn't you come to us?

963
01:26:43,143 --> 01:26:45,979
Well, er...

964
01:26:47,481 --> 01:26:50,734
I never met these gentlemen
before, sir, and...

965
01:26:50,859 --> 01:26:54,446
<i>er... you told... you... you...</i>

966
01:26:54,571 --> 01:26:58,617
you told Captain McClain that the Division
was clean as a hound's tooth.

967
01:26:58,742 --> 01:27:04,414
You think you're the only honest cop
on the force, Serpico? My record's clear.

968
01:27:04,540 --> 01:27:06,041
Inspector Gilbert's just come from

969
01:27:06,166 --> 01:27:09,586
the Commissioner's Confidential
Investigation Unit.

970
01:27:09,711 --> 01:27:12,047
Then you must have heard something.

971
01:27:14,967 --> 01:27:16,301
I don't understand.

972
01:27:16,426 --> 01:27:19,263
Commissioner Delaney has known
about this from the beginning.

973
01:27:21,557 --> 01:27:23,809
I didn't hear a thing.

974
01:27:23,934 --> 01:27:29,356
But I understand your frustration,
Frank, believe me.

975
01:27:29,481 --> 01:27:33,777
It's sort of like trying to punch
your way out of a paper bag, right?

976
01:27:38,031 --> 01:27:40,617
What outside agencies
have you been to, Frank?

977
01:27:48,375 --> 01:27:51,044
I don't see how that's pertinent
to my allegations.

978
01:27:52,379 --> 01:27:56,174
We ought to ask Serpico directly
if he's going to cooperate or not.

979
01:27:56,300 --> 01:28:00,512
We've got to know if there's
any real basis for an investigation.

980
01:28:04,099 --> 01:28:08,895
Well, l... l don't have to think that...
I have to think about that.

981
01:28:10,022 --> 01:28:12,274
What is there to think about?

982
01:28:13,275 --> 01:28:16,111
I don't see how the Division
can investigate itself.

983
01:28:17,946 --> 01:28:19,531
You've got a point there.

984
01:28:21,199 --> 01:28:23,910
But you would cooperate
with an impartial investigation, right?

985
01:28:27,581 --> 01:28:29,833
Yeah. Up to a point.

986
01:28:30,959 --> 01:28:32,753
As long as I'm not involved.

987
01:28:34,004 --> 01:28:37,674
I just want to go someplace
where I can do my job.

988
01:28:37,799 --> 01:28:39,676
That's fair enough.

989
01:28:40,469 --> 01:28:41,845
We'll be in touch.

990
01:28:46,642 --> 01:28:49,519
Inspector Palmer? May I see you?

991
01:28:56,109 --> 01:28:58,487
Was it necessary to let everyone
in the station house know

992
01:28:58,612 --> 01:29:01,114
I was coming to see these guys?

993
01:29:01,239 --> 01:29:04,242
You believe from what you now know
that an investigation is warranted?

994
01:29:05,827 --> 01:29:08,747
- Yes, Commissioner Delaney.
- Go to it.

995
01:29:12,793 --> 01:29:17,756
But sir, shouldn't Headquarters
handle something like this?

996
01:29:18,507 --> 01:29:22,010
No. You're all experienced men.

997
01:29:24,596 --> 01:29:27,099
Chief Gallagher here will be available
for consultation.

998
01:29:33,021 --> 01:29:34,481
Commissioner...

999
01:29:37,025 --> 01:29:39,528
Serpico claims that, er...

1000
01:29:40,821 --> 01:29:44,116
Inspector McClain talked to you
about this whole thing some time ago.

1001
01:29:44,241 --> 01:29:47,953
Yes. I seem to remember something about that.

1002
01:29:52,791 --> 01:29:56,837
We can't set up a surveillance on
"somewhere over by Crotona Park".

1003
01:29:56,962 --> 01:29:58,547
We need a location.

1004
01:29:59,297 --> 01:30:03,176
I've given you 36 locations
that are paying off. What do you want?

1005
01:30:03,301 --> 01:30:05,846
The whole thing signed, sealed, delivered?

1006
01:30:05,971 --> 01:30:08,098
You're conducting this investigation, not me.

1007
01:30:08,223 --> 01:30:11,101
All right, Frank. Lieutenant Smith.
Let's get back to him.

1008
01:30:11,226 --> 01:30:14,396
Lieutenant Smith. Lieutenant Smith said to me

1009
01:30:15,522 --> 01:30:19,484
if I didn't want the money,
he would stash it in his attic.

1010
01:30:20,068 --> 01:30:21,611
I'll have him transferred in the morning.

1011
01:30:21,737 --> 01:30:24,489
Fuck him. How about transferring me?

1012
01:30:33,540 --> 01:30:34,833
Serpico.

1013
01:30:36,960 --> 01:30:41,631
I hear you've been vouchering pad money
over to a confidential investigation squad.

1014
01:30:42,632 --> 01:30:44,217
Oh, yeah?

1015
01:30:44,342 --> 01:30:46,261
How can I voucher money
when I don't take any?

1016
01:30:47,471 --> 01:30:49,514
You won't find anything on Serpico.

1017
01:30:52,225 --> 01:30:54,978
He's clean. Right?

1018
01:30:58,482 --> 01:31:00,901
- Hm?
- You practising your frisk?

1019
01:31:02,402 --> 01:31:06,573
No. I'm looking to buy a used tape recorder.

1020
01:31:09,701 --> 01:31:13,789
Wear a wire? They're feeling me up
every day. How can I wear a wire?

1021
01:31:13,914 --> 01:31:15,957
Come on, Frank.

1022
01:31:16,082 --> 01:31:19,836
Look, wearing a wire means testifying
to corroborate the tape, right?

1023
01:31:19,961 --> 01:31:22,297
Right. I'm not testifying.

1024
01:31:23,715 --> 01:31:25,759
I've got to put a dime in the parking meter.

1025
01:31:25,884 --> 01:31:29,805
Franklin, put a dime
in the parking meter for Serpico.

1026
01:31:34,559 --> 01:31:39,272
Hey, Frank. Frank, you know
Herman Tauber, District Attorney.

1027
01:31:39,397 --> 01:31:40,982
Yeah, I watch television.

1028
01:31:41,441 --> 01:31:45,320
Frank, I want to compliment you
for coming forward like this.

1029
01:31:45,445 --> 01:31:48,824
It's unique. It's uniquely unique.

1030
01:31:48,949 --> 01:31:51,535
You should be proud of yourself.

1031
01:31:51,660 --> 01:31:54,454
There's gonna be a grand jury
on these shit heels,

1032
01:31:54,579 --> 01:31:57,707
with Frank Serpico as my star witness.

1033
01:31:57,833 --> 01:32:02,504
Mr Tauber, you and everybody in this
room can go to hell, cos I'm not testifying.

1034
01:32:02,629 --> 01:32:05,882
Wait, wait, wait. Just a second, Frank.

1035
01:32:06,007 --> 01:32:08,635
You have nothing to fear.
You're not gonna be singled out.

1036
01:32:08,760 --> 01:32:11,137
You don't understand. I'm not afraid.
I don't give a fuck who knows...

1037
01:32:11,263 --> 01:32:12,681
- Wait a minute.
- ...if it meant something.

1038
01:32:12,806 --> 01:32:15,350
- But this investigation is bullshit.
- Do you mind if I say something?

1039
01:32:15,475 --> 01:32:19,437
You're not going after corruption
in the Department, the Division, the Bronx.

1040
01:32:19,563 --> 01:32:23,692
A few flunkey cops thrown to the wolves
to protect Delaney and those guys.

1041
01:32:23,817 --> 01:32:26,361
They've known about this shit for years
and won't do a fucking thing about it.

1042
01:32:26,486 --> 01:32:27,863
That's why I won't testify.

1043
01:33:02,188 --> 01:33:03,857
OK, what's this?

1044
01:33:04,149 --> 01:33:06,735
Exactly what it says.

1045
01:33:06,860 --> 01:33:08,695
I'm splitting.

1046
01:33:09,154 --> 01:33:11,197
I've never read anything so stupid -

1047
01:33:11,323 --> 01:33:13,992
"I'm leaving. If you want to discuss it,
I'll be at Felix's."

1048
01:33:14,117 --> 01:33:16,369
I didn't feel like
another blood and gut scene.

1049
01:33:16,494 --> 01:33:20,707
- I figured you wouldn't be able to shout.
- I can shout anywhere!

1050
01:33:25,337 --> 01:33:27,339
I won't shout.

1051
01:33:28,882 --> 01:33:30,592
Sit down. Sit down.

1052
01:33:43,897 --> 01:33:47,901
It's just going to go on and on, Paco.
It isn't going to get any better.

1053
01:33:49,694 --> 01:33:52,781
And if you quit, somehow I'll be blamed.

1054
01:34:01,748 --> 01:34:05,669
How could you leave the man you love?
The future father of your kids?

1055
01:34:09,756 --> 01:34:12,300
You never said anything
like that to me before.

1056
01:34:14,135 --> 01:34:15,845
And if I come back...

1057
01:34:16,680 --> 01:34:18,014
you won't say it again.

1058
01:34:20,183 --> 01:34:23,561
You want to be free and unattached.

1059
01:34:23,687 --> 01:34:27,357
To go on fighting for your cause
and keep torturing yourself.

1060
01:34:27,482 --> 01:34:29,275
My cause...

1061
01:34:30,986 --> 01:34:32,696
Paco...

1062
01:34:33,530 --> 01:34:35,573
I felt so safe with you.

1063
01:34:35,699 --> 01:34:37,867
So loving.

1064
01:34:48,545 --> 01:34:50,088
Stay with me, Laurie.

1065
01:34:53,425 --> 01:34:55,343
- Come on. Stay with me.
- No. No.

1066
01:35:07,022 --> 01:35:10,150
What do l... owe you for that?

1067
01:35:24,039 --> 01:35:25,373
Laurie!

1068
01:35:31,546 --> 01:35:33,673
What are you doing?

1069
01:35:37,719 --> 01:35:39,471
Do you want to walk away or should I?

1070
01:35:41,306 --> 01:35:42,766
I'm not gonna walk away.

1071
01:35:45,310 --> 01:35:46,269
It's finished!

1072
01:35:54,277 --> 01:35:57,614
Who do you think you are pulling
that no testifying bullshit on me?

1073
01:35:57,739 --> 01:36:01,201
Chief Green, I know your reputation.

1074
01:36:01,326 --> 01:36:05,580
Look, maybe if you were borough
commander when this thing started,

1075
01:36:05,705 --> 01:36:09,334
running this investigation,
I'd feel different about testifying.

1076
01:36:09,459 --> 01:36:11,544
But you're coming in after the fact.

1077
01:36:11,669 --> 01:36:12,921
Cut the crap, Serpico.

1078
01:36:13,046 --> 01:36:16,091
You're like a quiff who says she won't,
then maybe she will, then she won't...

1079
01:36:16,216 --> 01:36:19,677
I'm like a quiff who's been fucked over
for a year and a half

1080
01:36:19,803 --> 01:36:22,847
by guys like Kellogg, McClain, Delaney...

1081
01:36:22,972 --> 01:36:25,683
I'm not Kellogg, McClain or Delaney.

1082
01:36:25,809 --> 01:36:30,188
Frank, it won't be just flunkey cops.
This is only the beginning.

1083
01:36:30,313 --> 01:36:33,149
This could be the biggest thing
since the Harry Gross case.

1084
01:36:33,274 --> 01:36:34,734
And meanwhile, where am I?

1085
01:36:34,859 --> 01:36:37,195
I'm out there alone.
Who gives a fuck about that?

1086
01:36:37,320 --> 01:36:40,115
I'm totally isolated in the Department.
I don't have a friend.

1087
01:36:40,240 --> 01:36:43,535
Don't give me that bullshit.
I've been putting cops away for 30 years.

1088
01:36:43,660 --> 01:36:47,080
My name's an obscenity
in every precinct in the city.

1089
01:36:47,205 --> 01:36:50,166
- I've observed that, sir.
- "Friends."

1090
01:36:50,291 --> 01:36:52,418
I fought my way up as a Jew in the days

1091
01:36:52,544 --> 01:36:55,463
when you were supposed to have
an uncircumcised shamrock.

1092
01:36:55,588 --> 01:36:59,175
I have this nightmare. I'm on Fifth Avenue
watching the St Patrick's Day Parade,

1093
01:36:59,300 --> 01:37:03,221
I have a coronary and 9,000 cops
march happily over my body.

1094
01:37:03,346 --> 01:37:07,225
- I haven't got a friend on the Force either.
- I'll be your friend, Chief.

1095
01:37:07,350 --> 01:37:10,145
I'm not looking for any.
I'll make an exception in your case.

1096
01:37:10,270 --> 01:37:11,729
Frank, you're a good cop.

1097
01:37:11,855 --> 01:37:14,774
<i>Stop being a prima donna.
Just cut out the shticklech.</i>

1098
01:37:14,899 --> 01:37:19,279
I don't understand. How am I being
a prima donna? I want to protect myself.

1099
01:37:19,904 --> 01:37:25,451
Frank, if we're gonna get the indictments,
you're gonna have to testify.

1100
01:37:33,543 --> 01:37:36,754
<i>Ready on the right. Ready on the left.</i>

1101
01:37:36,880 --> 01:37:39,090
<i>Ready on the firing line.</i>

1102
01:37:39,215 --> 01:37:40,341
(Buzzer)

1103
01:38:29,057 --> 01:38:32,477
What are you going to tell
the grand jury, Frankie?

1104
01:38:34,103 --> 01:38:36,022
Depends on what they ask me.

1105
01:38:36,147 --> 01:38:38,816
Suppose they ask you who's taking money.

1106
01:38:38,942 --> 01:38:42,612
- What I don't know I don't know.
- But you do know, Frank.

1107
01:38:43,696 --> 01:38:47,784
Frankie, I like you. I don't want
to see anything happen to you.

1108
01:38:47,909 --> 01:38:52,121
But you got to understand there are a lot
of people who could hurt you here.

1109
01:38:52,247 --> 01:38:55,833
I'm not saying it's going to happen,
I'm saying it could happen.

1110
01:38:55,959 --> 01:38:58,670
There's lots of ways.
Nobody has to take a shot at you.

1111
01:38:58,795 --> 01:39:00,922
They can just not be there
when you need them.

1112
01:39:01,047 --> 01:39:04,175
If somebody comes at you with a gun,
they look the other way.

1113
01:39:04,300 --> 01:39:06,469
Or they'll send you in first enough times

1114
01:39:06,594 --> 01:39:09,597
until finally one day you're gonna walk
in the wrong door.

1115
01:39:12,809 --> 01:39:15,436
- Thanks for the information.
- Fuck you, Frank.

1116
01:39:18,690 --> 01:39:21,317
I have nothing more.
Does anyone have any further questions?

1117
01:39:21,442 --> 01:39:24,570
Er... yes. If I may, Mr Knowles. Thank you.

1118
01:39:24,696 --> 01:39:29,158
Officer Serpico came to the 7th Division
more than a year and a half ago.

1119
01:39:29,284 --> 01:39:32,704
All during that time,
the things he's told us were taking place.

1120
01:39:32,829 --> 01:39:38,001
Now, why didn't Officer Serpico report
these criminal activities long before,

1121
01:39:38,126 --> 01:39:40,753
- when he first encountered them?
- I'd like to answer that.

1122
01:39:40,878 --> 01:39:47,719
Mrs Crist's question I don't believe is
material or relevant to the present inquiry.

1123
01:39:47,844 --> 01:39:49,971
I'd like to answer that question.

1124
01:39:50,096 --> 01:39:53,599
Officer Serpico cannot be considered
derelict of his duty in any way

1125
01:39:53,725 --> 01:39:57,854
or guilty of any infraction of the law -
quite the contrary.

1126
01:39:57,979 --> 01:40:01,232
District Attorney is not prepared
to say any more at this time.

1127
01:40:01,357 --> 01:40:04,944
Very well, Mr Tauber. Officer Serpico,
thank you for your testimony.

1128
01:40:05,069 --> 01:40:07,947
This hearing is adjourned
until 10:00 tomorrow morning.

1129
01:40:09,240 --> 01:40:12,618
Why didn't you tell him
about Delaney and Kellogg?

1130
01:40:12,744 --> 01:40:16,998
Frank, this was a grand jury about police
officers actively engaged in corruption.

1131
01:40:18,291 --> 01:40:20,877
You don't implicate people
without sufficient evidence.

1132
01:40:21,002 --> 01:40:23,171
That's crap and you know it.

1133
01:40:23,296 --> 01:40:27,091
Even a dumb cop like me knows
a prosecutor can take a grand jury

1134
01:40:27,216 --> 01:40:28,801
anywhere it wants to take it.

1135
01:40:28,926 --> 01:40:31,429
You never let me anywhere near
the real problems.

1136
01:40:31,554 --> 01:40:34,766
Nothing about the bosses, the brass,

1137
01:40:34,891 --> 01:40:37,685
how corruption like this could exist
without anybody knowing about it.

1138
01:40:37,810 --> 01:40:40,438
A few flunkey cops in the Bronx, that's it.

1139
01:40:40,563 --> 01:40:43,066
None of the shit
in Queens, Brooklyn, Manhattan...

1140
01:40:43,191 --> 01:40:44,484
Don't forget Kansas City.

1141
01:40:44,609 --> 01:40:48,696
- "The biggest thing since Harry Gross"?
- All right!

1142
01:40:48,821 --> 01:40:54,077
Look, Frank. You've got guts. Integrity.

1143
01:40:54,202 --> 01:40:57,163
There's going to be
a detective's gold shield in this for you.

1144
01:40:59,665 --> 01:41:02,126
That's terrific. That's good.

1145
01:41:03,294 --> 01:41:06,881
Maybe this is what it's all about.
I should take my gold shield and forget it.

1146
01:41:07,006 --> 01:41:09,300
I know you've been through an ordeal, Frank.

1147
01:41:11,886 --> 01:41:15,223
I'm a marked man in this Department,
for what?

1148
01:41:15,348 --> 01:41:18,976
- I've already arranged a transfer for you.
- To where? China?

1149
01:41:30,655 --> 01:41:35,576
That takes a 14-shot clip.
You expecting an army?

1150
01:41:35,701 --> 01:41:37,620
No, just a Division.

1151
01:41:39,789 --> 01:41:44,127
Tauber, did you know I've had reports
about Serpico being a fag?

1152
01:41:44,252 --> 01:41:46,754
He used to hang out in the BCI washroom.

1153
01:41:46,879 --> 01:41:48,881
That's stupid, Commissioner, and you know it.

1154
01:41:50,883 --> 01:41:56,180
Commissioner, a gold shield for Serpico at
this time would convince a lot of people...

1155
01:41:56,305 --> 01:41:57,723
Not while I'm commissioner.

1156
01:42:16,826 --> 01:42:18,828
Commander's office?

1157
01:42:20,705 --> 01:42:22,748
It's down that corridor.

1158
01:42:25,585 --> 01:42:28,588
Hey, Serpico, do you know
what they're saying in the Bronx?

1159
01:42:29,172 --> 01:42:31,507
That you spilled your guts to the grand jury.

1160
01:42:32,383 --> 01:42:34,427
Say it isn't so, Serpico.

1161
01:42:36,429 --> 01:42:38,347
It isn't so.

1162
01:42:39,432 --> 01:42:41,767
We know how to handle guys like you.

1163
01:42:42,643 --> 01:42:44,228
I ought to cut your tongue out.

1164
01:42:46,481 --> 01:42:48,149
(Shouting)

1165
01:42:50,568 --> 01:42:52,236
Don't move.

1166
01:43:08,669 --> 01:43:10,463
(Knocking)

1167
01:43:14,217 --> 01:43:16,844
