1229
01:48:48,551 --> 01:48:50,845
I don't know if the timing is right.

1230
01:48:53,889 --> 01:48:59,019
I want it to get on the record, that's all.
In case something should happen to me.

1231
01:49:02,690 --> 01:49:04,608
I want it on the record.

1232
01:49:07,736 --> 01:49:09,446
I don't know if we carry enough weight.

1233
01:49:10,948 --> 01:49:15,870
I don't know if the Times will go out on
a limb on the say-so of two flunkey cops.

1234
01:49:19,623 --> 01:49:22,543
Suppose an inspector were to come with us.

1235
01:49:23,627 --> 01:49:25,796
You know, I got 20 years on the Force.

1236
01:49:25,921 --> 01:49:30,593
We just got this place and signed
a 500-year mortgage on it.

1237
01:49:30,718 --> 01:49:33,721
- (Television blares)
- Will you turn that thing off out there!

1238
01:49:33,846 --> 01:49:36,265
- OK, come on. Everybody to bed.
- Oh, Mum!

1239
01:49:36,390 --> 01:49:38,809
- Turn that damn thing down.
- Come on, now. Go on upstairs.

1240
01:49:39,268 --> 01:49:41,562
You said we could go to bed late!

1241
01:49:42,897 --> 01:49:45,941
This is against Department regulations.
You both know that.

1242
01:49:46,066 --> 01:49:49,278
If they want to throw the book at me
they can do it.

1243
01:49:50,446 --> 01:49:52,489
If I left the Force...

1244
01:49:53,866 --> 01:49:55,784
I don't know what I could do.

1245
01:50:01,582 --> 01:50:04,919
OK, I've made my little speech.
I'll back you up 100 per cent.

1246
01:50:09,882 --> 01:50:12,760
<i>Times and the News.
I got the money, fellas.</i>

1247
01:50:12,885 --> 01:50:14,929
There you go. There you go. There you go.

1248
01:50:15,054 --> 01:50:16,805
<i>Newsweek, please.</i>

1249
01:50:18,682 --> 01:50:20,476
Holy shit!

1250
01:50:23,020 --> 01:50:27,691
Oh, Christ. You can almost predict
the numbers they're going to do.

1251
01:50:27,816 --> 01:50:29,985
Delaney's going to issue some phoney denial.

1252
01:50:30,110 --> 01:50:32,947
Somebody from the Mayor's office
will say something noble.

1253
01:50:33,072 --> 01:50:35,449
Delaney will change his tune.

1254
01:50:35,574 --> 01:50:37,451
And finally, the Mayor
is gonna appoint a commission.

1255
01:50:37,576 --> 01:50:41,163
"Thursday Mayor Lindsay announced
the formation of a five-man committee

1256
01:50:41,288 --> 01:50:44,208
"to review the City procedures
when investigating police corruption."

1257
01:50:44,333 --> 01:50:48,420
- How come I'm not in the first paragraph?
- Unbelievable!

1258
01:50:48,545 --> 01:50:51,840
Yihoo! Yihoo! Yihoo!

1259
01:50:52,967 --> 01:50:57,262
<i>The Times report smells
of the familiar smear tactics</i>

1260
01:50:57,388 --> 01:50:59,473
<i>of McCarthyism.</i>

1261
01:50:59,598 --> 01:51:03,352
I have issued a statement to be read
at every station...

1262
01:51:03,477 --> 01:51:06,814
The Mayor is appointing
a special investigation commission

1263
01:51:06,939 --> 01:51:09,650
<i>- to be headed by Whitman Knapp.</i>
- Yeah, come.

1264
01:51:15,155 --> 01:51:19,702
Here's your reward, Frank.
It's a transfer to Narcotics, Brooklyn South.

1265
01:51:20,786 --> 01:51:23,831
Still in Clothes.
You get a tin shield, not a gold one.

1266
01:51:28,711 --> 01:51:30,087
I miss you already, Frank.

1267
01:51:35,634 --> 01:51:37,177
Look...

1268
01:51:37,845 --> 01:51:39,763
Frank...

1269
01:51:41,598 --> 01:51:45,352
It's Narcotics. Be careful.

1270
01:51:47,021 --> 01:51:49,815
It's very easy to, erm... get hurt.

1271
01:51:51,817 --> 01:51:53,569
You know, to, er...

1272
01:51:55,029 --> 01:51:56,739
to be set up.

1273
01:52:21,680 --> 01:52:24,224
(indistinct police radio)

1274
01:52:36,445 --> 01:52:37,654
Serpico!

1275
01:52:38,864 --> 01:52:40,866
Get in.

1276
01:52:57,591 --> 01:52:59,593
You're not wired, are you?

1277
01:53:01,053 --> 01:53:03,388
OK, you cocksucker.

1278
01:53:04,264 --> 01:53:07,142
You might get by in the Bronx
with that kind of shit,

1279
01:53:07,267 --> 01:53:10,854
but down here 800 a month is chicken feed.

1280
01:53:12,356 --> 01:53:17,402
Last week one dope dealer sent out
these guys making pick-ups.

1281
01:53:18,237 --> 01:53:20,656
40,000 each.

1282
01:53:20,781 --> 01:53:24,368
We let them collect it all and then hit them.

1283
01:53:24,493 --> 01:53:27,955
120,000 split four ways.

1284
01:53:28,956 --> 01:53:31,083
That's serious money.

1285
01:53:31,208 --> 01:53:33,836
And with that, you don't fuck around.

1286
01:53:36,463 --> 01:53:38,382
I got the message.

1287
01:53:38,549 --> 01:53:41,468
Good. Now get the fuck out.

1288
01:53:48,225 --> 01:53:51,895
The guy's name is Limbo. He always uses
his girlfriend's brother's place.

1289
01:53:52,020 --> 01:53:54,606
He's a pusher. Heroin.

1290
01:53:54,731 --> 01:53:58,861
We're going to drive round to the corner.
You keep in sight, out front.

1291
01:53:58,986 --> 01:54:02,614
When you spot somebody who's dirty,
you take off your glasses and wipe them.

1292
01:54:02,739 --> 01:54:04,700
Right. OK.

1293
01:55:13,894 --> 01:55:16,230
If we stay around here very long,
we'll get spotted.

1294
01:55:16,355 --> 01:55:19,983
Well, Frank, why don't you go up there
and check it out?

1295
01:55:20,108 --> 01:55:23,362
- Why don't you?
- I got the wrong clothes.

1296
01:55:23,487 --> 01:55:26,156
- I'll take you shopping.
- Uh-huh.

1297
01:57:02,419 --> 01:57:03,920
(Dog barking)

1298
01:57:09,968 --> 01:57:11,970
- (Knocking)
- Limbo?

1299
01:57:13,597 --> 01:57:15,432
(Speaks Spanish)

1300
01:57:45,462 --> 01:57:47,464
Police! Freeze!

1301
01:57:47,589 --> 01:57:50,384
Police Officer. Up against the wall.
Get your hands up.

1302
01:57:52,344 --> 01:57:55,180
All right. Palms up on the wall
and spread them.

1303
01:57:55,305 --> 01:57:58,892
Get them up! Get your hands up!
Come on! Get your feet apart!

1304
01:57:59,810 --> 01:58:01,520
- I saw the buy.
- All right, let's get Limbo.

1305
01:58:01,645 --> 01:58:04,356
- Julio, you all right, baby?
- Yeah, I got them.

1306
01:58:48,442 --> 01:58:50,777
(Speaks Spanish)

1307
01:59:08,420 --> 01:59:10,213
Police officer!

1308
01:59:13,383 --> 01:59:15,427
(Shouting in Spanish)

1309
01:59:20,223 --> 01:59:22,350
What the fuck are you waiting for?

1310
01:59:22,476 --> 01:59:24,436
(Continues in Spanish)

1311
01:59:41,369 --> 01:59:44,247
Police! Drop your guns
and come out with your hands up!

1312
02:00:19,866 --> 02:00:22,827
- What have we got here?
- It's Mr and Mrs Serpico, sir.

1313
02:00:22,953 --> 02:00:24,704
OK. Go ahead.

1314
02:00:28,124 --> 02:00:30,919
- Yes?
- Where's our son?

1315
02:00:31,044 --> 02:00:33,880
- They're bringing him down from X-Ray.
- We want to see him.

1316
02:00:34,005 --> 02:00:36,174
Just a few minutes.

1317
02:01:03,535 --> 02:01:08,081
Mr and Mrs Serpico,
the news is better than we expected.

1318
02:01:09,666 --> 02:01:14,004
Thank God the bullet was a small calibre.

1319
02:01:14,129 --> 02:01:15,714
It didn't enter the brain.

1320
02:01:15,839 --> 02:01:19,426
- (Translates)
- Or strike the spinal cord.

1321
02:01:20,969 --> 02:01:23,346
He's on the critical list.

1322
02:01:23,471 --> 02:01:26,516
But his condition seems to be stable.

1323
02:01:28,018 --> 02:01:29,978
Thank you, Doctor. Thank you.

1324
02:02:03,845 --> 02:02:06,389
Stay out of there. Didn't they tell you?

1325
02:02:07,057 --> 02:02:10,268
- What?
- The word is don't talk to him.

1326
02:02:10,393 --> 02:02:12,354
He's no fucking good.

1327
02:02:21,780 --> 02:02:23,948
- How you doing, kid?
- Hello, Sid.

1328
02:02:31,081 --> 02:02:32,874
Come over here.

1329
02:02:36,211 --> 02:02:38,755
Want to read my fan mail?

1330
02:02:38,880 --> 02:02:42,092
Sure. You're a big shot now, huh?

1331
02:03:07,325 --> 02:03:09,369
Sid...

1332
02:03:11,246 --> 02:03:14,499
I want you to get those fucking cops
away from my door.

1333
02:03:25,427 --> 02:03:29,013
The Knapp Commission likes you.
They want you to appear.

1334
02:03:29,139 --> 02:03:30,807
Naturally.

1335
02:03:34,894 --> 02:03:39,649
Frank, Heinemann and Julio are cleared.
You're up for exceptional merit awards.

1336
02:03:41,109 --> 02:03:42,569
That's very funny.

1337
02:03:48,283 --> 02:03:50,326
That's very funny.

1338
02:03:51,870 --> 02:03:53,663
Francesco, you love me?

1339
02:03:55,915 --> 02:03:58,376
I always had a thing for you, Sid,
you know that.

1340
02:04:02,547 --> 02:04:04,799
Your gold shield's come through.

1341
02:04:33,536 --> 02:04:35,580
What's this for?

1342
02:04:39,042 --> 02:04:41,711
For being an honest cop?

1343
02:04:41,836 --> 02:04:43,254
Hm?

1344
02:04:44,130 --> 02:04:47,175
Or for being stupid enough
to get shot in the face?

1345
02:04:51,763 --> 02:04:54,682
You tell them they can shove it.

1346
02:05:00,396 --> 02:05:02,398
I don't want it.

1347
02:05:41,020 --> 02:05:43,147
Oh, well.

1348
02:05:47,235 --> 02:05:49,487
Well, Frank, the facts are these.

1349
02:05:50,363 --> 02:05:54,158
You'll have to stay on leave of absence
for a few months.

1350
02:05:54,284 --> 02:05:57,912
In all probability, the hearing
in your left ear won't come back.

1351
02:05:58,037 --> 02:06:00,665
Two bullet fragments are still lodged there
in the bony portion.

1352
02:06:00,790 --> 02:06:02,670
One is very close to the carotid artery

1353
02:06:02,696 --> 02:06:05,153
<i>and you'll have to be checked from time to time.</i>

1354
02:06:05,253 --> 02:06:07,755
<i>Your left side will feel stiff occasionally.</i>

1355
02:06:08,798 --> 02:06:11,843
<i>Once in a great while you may experience
some dizziness.</i>

1356
02:06:11,968 --> 02:06:15,013
<i>But in general, you'll be OK.</i>

1357
02:06:32,697 --> 02:06:34,782
Through my appearance here today,

1358
02:06:34,908 --> 02:06:36,951
I hope that police officers in the future

1359
02:06:37,076 --> 02:06:41,915
will not experience the same frustration
and anxiety that I was subjected to

1360
02:06:42,040 --> 02:06:45,126
for the past five years
at the hands of my superiors

1361
02:06:45,251 --> 02:06:48,129
because of my attempt to report corruption.

1362
02:06:48,254 --> 02:06:53,009
I was made to feel that I had burdened
them with an unwanted task.

1363
02:06:53,134 --> 02:06:56,512
The problem is that the atmosphere
does not yet exist

1364
02:06:56,638 --> 02:07:00,892
in which an honest police officer can act
without fear of ridicule or reprisal

1365
02:07:01,017 --> 02:07:03,269
from fellow officers.

1366
02:07:03,394 --> 02:07:07,023
Police corruption cannot exist
unless it is at least tolerated

1367
02:07:07,148 --> 02:07:09,150
at higher levels in the Department.

1368
02:07:09,275 --> 02:07:12,487
Therefore the most important result
that can come from these hearings

1369
02:07:12,612 --> 02:07:16,908
is a conviction by police officers
that the Department will change.

1370
02:07:17,784 --> 02:07:22,038
In order to ensure this, an independent,
permanent investigative body

1371
02:07:22,163 --> 02:07:25,833
dealing with police corruption
like this commission, is essential.

1372
02:07:25,959 --> 02:07:28,294
(Applause)


